<main class="main-content main-content--dashboard">
  <div class="c-toolbar">
    <div class="c-toolbar__row items-center w-full gap-3">
      <%= link_to "Back to batches", admin_grade_import_batches_path, class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary) %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="c-container c-container--wide c-page">
    <section class="u-stack u-stack--lg">
      <header class="c-card p-6 md:p-8 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200">
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">New Grade Import Batch</h1>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Upload workbooks and preview matches before committing.</p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_320px]">
        <section class="c-card p-6 md:p-8 u-stack u-stack--md">
          <div>
            <h2 class="c-section-title c-heading-inline">Upload & Preview</h2>
          </div>

          <%= form_with url: admin_grade_import_batches_path, method: :post, local: true, multipart: true, class: "u-stack u-stack--md" do %>
            <div class="u-grid" style="--u-grid-min: 320px">
              <div class="c-field">
                <%= label_tag :program_semester_id, "Program semester", class: "c-label" %>
                <%= select_tag :program_semester_id,
                      options_from_collection_for_select(ProgramSemester.ordered, :id, :name, ProgramSemester.current&.id),
                      include_blank: "No semester",
                      class: "c-input" %>
                <small class="c-help">Used to associate competency sources on the student dashboard.</small>
              </div>

              <div class="c-field">
                <%= label_tag "files[]", "Upload files (Excel or CSV)", class: "c-label" %>
                <%= file_field_tag "files[]", multiple: true, accept: ".xlsx,.xlsm,.csv", class: "c-input" %>
                <small class="c-help">Select one or more files.</small>
              </div>

              <div class="c-field">
                <%= label_tag "folder_files[]", "Or upload a folder", class: "c-label" %>
                <%= file_field_tag "folder_files[]", multiple: true, webkitdirectory: true, directory: true, class: "c-input" %>
                <small class="c-help">One workbook per course.</small>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-t pt-4">
              <label class="c-toggle cursor-pointer">
                <%= check_box_tag :dry_run, "1", true, class: "c-toggle__input" %>
                <span class="c-toggle__track" aria-hidden="true"><span class="c-toggle__thumb"></span></span>
                <span class="space-y-0.5">
                  <span class="c-toggle__label block">Preview first</span>
                  <span class="block text-xs text-slate-600">Review matches and derived ratings before committing.</span>
                </span>
              </label>
            </div>

            <div class="c-form-actions u-actions u-actions--start">
              <%= submit_tag "Run Import", class: tailwind_button_classes(:primary) %>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </section>

        <aside class="u-stack u-stack--sm">
          <div class="c-card c-card--tight border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/70 u-stack u-stack--xs">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Upload options</p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-slate-700 space-y-1">
              <li><strong>Canvas grades:</strong> Direct export with mapping sheet</li>
              <li><strong>Canvas competencies:</strong> Direct competency export</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="c-card c-card--tight u-stack u-stack--xs">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Examples</p>
            <div class="u-actions u-actions--start space-y-2 flex flex-col">
              <%= link_to "Grade Export",
                          "/grade-import-examples/Example%20Canvas%20Grade%20Export.xlsx",
                          class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary),
                          data: { turbo: false },
                          download: true %>
              <%= link_to "Competency Export",
                          "/grade-import-examples/Example%20Canvas%20Competency%20Export.csv",
                          class: tailwind_button_classes(:secondary),
                          data: { turbo: false },
                          download: true %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <details class="c-card c-card--tight c-card--muted u-stack u-stack--xs">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer text-xs font-semibold text-slate-900">View guide</summary>
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-white p-3 text-xs text-slate-700 mt-2" data-controller="markdown-render">
              <textarea class="hidden" data-markdown-render-target="source"># Grade Import Guide

## Option 1: Canvas direct grade export
- Include Student ID and assignment columns
- Add a `mapping` sheet with:
  - `assignment_match_type` (exact/contains/regex)
  - `assignment_match_value` (name or pattern)
  - `course_code` (format ABCD-000-000)
  - `competency_title` (exact match required)
  - `score_basis` (points or percent)
  - `min_score`, `max_score`, `competency_level`

## Option 2: Canvas competency export
- Keep Student ID and competency result columns
- Course code derived from file/sheet name
- No mapping sheet required

## Approved competency titles
- Public and Population Health Assessment
- Delivery, Organization, and Financing of Health Services and Health Systems
- Policy Analysis
- Legal and Ethical Bases for Health Services and Health Systems
- Ethics, Accountability, and Self-Assessment
- Organizational Dynamics
- Problem Solving, Decision Making, and Critical Thinking
- Team Building and Collaboration
- Strategic Planning
- Business Planning
- Communication
- Financial Management
- Performance Improvement
- Project Management
- Systems Thinking
- Data Analysis and Information Management
- Quantitative Methods for Health Services Delivery

## Workflow
1. Run as Preview to review matches and ratings
2. Make corrections if needed
3. Re-upload to commit</textarea>
              <div class="guidance-text" data-markdown-render-target="output"></div>
            </div>
          </details>
        </aside>
    </section>
  </div>
</main>
